&lt;p>According to my kids, I get paid to &amp;ldquo;talk and draw boxes.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>They aren&amp;rsquo;t wrong. After two and a half decades in the industry, I’ve realized that the most complex problems in the world are usually just a bunch of messy, disconnected boxes waiting for someone to draw the right lines between them.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>